comments.body:
I am fine if we block `--userns` within a pod, but I am not sure about blocking the command reported in the issue.

The user's intentions are clear with the command `podman run --userns keep-id --network container:other-container ...` and the kernel allows that, and we artificially block it.

@TristanCacqueray what is your use case for using both `--userns keep-id` and `--network container:other-container`?
